OSOGBO – The Minister of Interior, Ogbeni Rauf Aregbesola, has hinted that he is fully behind one of the factional caucuses of Osun State All Progressives Congress (APC) otherwise called, The Osun Progressives (TOP). Aregbesola made the declaration on Friday at Ilesa, Osun State during the commissioning of Digital Nigeria Centre in Ilesa, Osun State. The Minister said it is no longer news that Osun APC is divided into factions and I am fully behind one of the factions known as TOP. Haaland Double As Dortmund Put 5 Past Freiburg AFCON: Gabon’s Late Strike Earns Draw Against Ghana In… He said, “I belong to TOP, the group established to correct the wrong within the APC. I greet the Chairman of APC, Honourable Rasaki Salinsile, the Chairman of my own APC in Osun”. This declaration has put an end to the rumour that he may not be supporting the activities of the splinter group within the Osun APC. Recall that there was a parallel APC congress in Osun where members loyal to Aregbesola are in one of the camps while those loyal to Governor Oyetola are in another camp called “Ileri Oluwa”. Aregbesola has revealed that he is fully with Osun Progressives TOP, a faction within All Progressives Congress (APC) in the state Osun. The Minister also stated that the ruling party in the State of Osun APC has two factions in the state. POLL He said the party is divided into two factions. Aregbesola also announced that he is fully with The Osun Progressives TOP and its activities. He said, “The party is divided in Osun. Salinsile is the Chairman of the Ogbeni Rauf Aregbesola faction of the APC. We were here for 8 years. We worked tirelessly and there was no glitch here. So, it is not out of place when we seek to reform things here. The party here is two now.”